2
00:00:42.252 --> 00:00:45.255
This guy die or something?
'Cause I get queasy.

3
00:00:45.839 --> 00:00:47.131
If he did. you got to tell me now

4
00:00:47.132 --> 00:00:49.216
'cause I can't be
walking in with no dead body.

5
00:00:49.217 --> 00:00:51.927
I do locks and light bulbs.
Blood isn't my thing.

6
00:00:51.928 --> 00:00:53.262
Can you open it or not?

7
00:00:53.263 --> 00:00:56.308
Yeah. I'm trying
but these keys aren't working.

8
00:00:59.853 --> 00:01:01.645
Was this Trumbull guy Judicial?

9
00:01:01.646 --> 00:01:04.982
- I'm not at liberty to...
- If so. I'll need a different set.

10
00:01:04.983 --> 00:01:06.567
Maybe tomorrow we can come back...

11
00:01:06.568 --> 00:01:08.861
- With the Forgiveness Holiday...
- Is there another way in?

12
00:01:08.862 --> 00:01:11.113
- Yeah. but Judge Meadows...
- Sheriff. Hey...

13
00:01:11.114 --> 00:01:13.450
What are you... Wait. what are you...

14
00:01:17.913 --> 00:01:19.914
IT distro probably cut the power early.

15
00:01:19.915 --> 00:01:22.416
Yeah. but protocol requires
the power be on...

16
00:01:22.417 --> 00:01:24.710
Can you head to distro
and get the lights back on?

17
00:01:24.711 --> 00:01:26.129
- Yeah.
- Great.

18
00:01:26.838 --> 00:01:28.923
You two take the kitchen.
I'm gonna check the bedroom.

19
00:01:28.924 --> 00:01:31.842
- What are we looking for?
- For anything strange

20
00:01:31.843 --> 00:01:33.970
that might tell us
why Trumbull killed Marnes.

21
00:01:51.238 --> 00:01:53.739
- You go in there yet?
- No. Anything in the front?

22
00:01:53.740 --> 00:01:54.991
Not yet.

23
00:02:08.295 --> 00:02:09.838
What the heck is this?

24
00:02:12.008 --> 00:02:14.135
- What you got?
- Honestly. I don't know.

25
00:02:15.387 --> 00:02:16.388
But...

26
00:02:19.641 --> 00:02:21.142
We're gonna need a relics bag.

27
00:04:17.466 --> 00:04:18.802
What are you smiling at?

28
00:04:21.680 --> 00:04:22.681
At you. I guess.

29
00:04:23.890 --> 00:04:26.184
You know they call you
Creepy George. right?

30
00:04:26.893 --> 00:04:28.978
They've scratched it on the side
of the generator.

31
00:04:28.979 --> 00:04:31.397
- It says. "Beware of Creepy George."
- Okay. First off...

32
00:04:31.398 --> 00:04:33.316
- "He is so creepy."
- ...you shut up.

33
00:04:33.817 --> 00:04:36.944
- You would never allow generator graffiti.
- Yeah. that's true.

34
00:04:36.945 --> 00:04:37.861
And second.

35
00:04:37.862 --> 00:04:41.365
if you'd said. "creepy computer guy."
I might have believed you.

36
00:04:41.366 --> 00:04:44.244
In fact. Creepy George.
if he really is a thing.

37
00:04:45.996 --> 00:04:47.247
probably just another guy.

38
00:04:47.914 --> 00:04:51.458
Am I your only friend? Like.
I know I'm your only friend down here.

39
00:04:51.459 --> 00:04:55.129
but am I your only friend
in the entire Silo?

40
00:04:55.130 --> 00:04:56.798
'Cause that's pretty sad.

41
00:04:57.674 --> 00:04:59.926
No. It's pretty great.

42
00:05:02.095 --> 00:05:04.055
I mean. if I gotta have one.

43
00:05:09.102 --> 00:05:10.270
You wanna keep that?

44
00:05:11.897 --> 00:05:15.274
What. if I wanna risk going to prison
or sent down to the mines

45
00:05:15.275 --> 00:05:17.986
for one of your strange toys? No.

46
00:05:18.486 --> 00:05:21.906
We already broke into Supply together
so you could have your precious tape.

47
00:05:21.907 --> 00:05:26.160
No. so Mechanical and the Silo
could have its necessary tape.

48
00:05:26.161 --> 00:05:29.163
- And you. sir. did nothing.
- Hey.

49
00:05:29.164 --> 00:05:30.707
No. You drew a map.

50
00:05:31.207 --> 00:05:33.626
A really shitty map.
I did everything else by myself.

51
00:05:33.627 --> 00:05:36.795
including throwing bacon at dogs
and running like crazy.

52
00:05:36.796 --> 00:05:38.256
But for a roll of tape.

53
00:05:39.674 --> 00:05:42.469
George. that tape saves lives. okay?

54
00:05:43.595 --> 00:05:45.179
Maybe not IT's shitty tape.

55
00:05:45.180 --> 00:05:47.848
but Mechanical's does.
and that's why I did it.

56
00:05:47.849 --> 00:05:50.936
I didn't take a risk for myself.

57
00:05:52.979 --> 00:05:54.146
I did it for everyone.

58
00:05:54.147 --> 00:05:59.235
and these strange things you have here.

59
00:05:59.236 --> 00:06:01.195
they're just not worth risking a life for.

60
00:06:01.196 --> 00:06:02.696
Especially when you don't know
what they are.

61
00:06:02.697 --> 00:06:06.701
If these things aren't worth
risking our lives for.

62
00:06:07.702 --> 00:06:10.288
why do they make it a risk to our lives
to have them?

63
00:06:13.959 --> 00:06:15.292
I don't know.

64
00:06:15.293 --> 00:06:16.378
Neither do I.

65
00:06:17.796 --> 00:06:22.759
These things were used by someone
for something at some point as tools.

66
00:06:23.343 --> 00:06:24.677
I'm gonna use 'em as clues.

67
00:06:24.678 --> 00:06:26.345
It's a stupidly dangerous hobby.

68
00:06:26.346 --> 00:06:30.183
And not all of these things are illegal.
by the way.

69
00:06:30.850 --> 00:06:31.851
Okay.

70
00:06:34.187 --> 00:06:35.397
This...

71
00:06:36.606 --> 00:06:43.279
may not appear as valuable
as a refurbished socket wrench

72
00:06:43.280 --> 00:06:48.284
or as romantic as flowers from the Mids.

73
00:06:48.285 --> 00:06:50.662
But to me. this watch...

74
00:06:53.623 --> 00:06:54.708
is everything.

75
00:06:59.462 --> 00:07:01.172
And I want to give it to you.

76
00:07:12.183 --> 00:07:14.685
George. it's broken.

77
00:07:14.686 --> 00:07:18.939
No. I'm serious. It's like a paperweight
cheaper than the paper it would hold up.

78
00:07:18.940 --> 00:07:20.358
It's a gift.

79
00:07:23.069 --> 00:07:27.031
And in a world filled with a million
unknowns. it is possible that this watch

80
00:07:27.032 --> 00:07:29.783
and crazy relics like these...

81
00:07:29.784 --> 00:07:31.493
- George.
- ...are the key to answering

82
00:07:31.494 --> 00:07:33.203
- the Silo's biggest questions.
- George.

83
00:07:33.204 --> 00:07:35.581
Are you not gonna ask
what the Silo's biggest question is?

84
00:07:35.582 --> 00:07:37.208
Just stop talking. please.

85
00:07:38.585 --> 00:07:39.920
Before you fuck it all up.

86
00:08:57.747 --> 00:08:58.957
Shit.

87
00:08:59.791 --> 00:09:01.750
You didn't take that to Judicial?

88
00:09:01.751 --> 00:09:03.168
You're in early.

89
00:09:03.169 --> 00:09:04.546
First day you beat me in.

90
00:09:05.881 --> 00:09:07.590
Is that a note for me?

91
00:09:07.591 --> 00:09:09.551
A porter brought it from Recycling.

92
00:09:13.013 --> 00:09:15.890
Keeping an illegal relic
beyond the 12-hour window

93
00:09:15.891 --> 00:09:18.852
from discovery to Judicial handoff
is a serious crime.

94
00:09:19.352 --> 00:09:20.520
Even for a sheriff.

95
00:09:22.105 --> 00:09:24.649
- How do you know it's illegal?
- I know that I don't know.

96
00:09:25.233 --> 00:09:29.904
Clause 75A-11: An investigation
into relics may be conducted

97
00:09:29.905 --> 00:09:32.948
by either the sheriff
or the Judicial Department when the re...

98
00:09:32.949 --> 00:09:35.576
When the identified relic
is associated with a serious crime.

99
00:09:35.577 --> 00:09:37.119
I'd say murder qualifies.

100
00:09:37.120 --> 00:09:40.414
You read the next paragraph?
That's only with Judicial's approval.

101
00:09:40.415 --> 00:09:41.916
Which means?

102
00:09:41.917 --> 00:09:45.212
If you want a relics investigation.
you have to see Judge Meadows.

103
00:09:46.129 --> 00:09:49.548
I'm hearing that a lot. Why don't they rip
the pages out of the Pact

104
00:09:49.549 --> 00:09:51.760
and leave one that says.
"See Judge Meadows"?

105
00:09:52.719 --> 00:09:53.928
You've talked to her. right?

106
00:09:53.929 --> 00:09:56.430
She'd pass through the office
when I was at Judicial.

107
00:09:56.431 --> 00:09:58.807
But these days.
even when you win the Pact competition.

108
00:09:58.808 --> 00:10:00.309
it's Sims who gives you the pin.

109
00:10:00.310 --> 00:10:03.479
There's a competition
for knowing the Pact?

110
00:10:03.480 --> 00:10:04.563
I won it four times.

111
00:10:04.564 --> 00:10:06.983
- More than anyone else.
- Of course you did.

112
00:10:07.817 --> 00:10:10.527
But I was just a Judicial regular.

113
00:10:10.528 --> 00:10:11.779
You're the sheriff.

114
00:10:11.780 --> 00:10:14.324
If you wanna meet with Meadows.
that's another thing entirely.

115
00:10:17.869 --> 00:10:22.666
Happy Forgiveness Day.
Today is for unity. family and friends.

116
00:10:24.125 --> 00:10:25.710
- Happy Forgiveness Day.
- Good morning.

117
00:10:27.837 --> 00:10:30.048
- Billings. Sheriff.
- Sims.

118
00:10:33.301 --> 00:10:34.803
- How are things?
- Good.

119
00:10:35.428 --> 00:10:37.847
- How's Judicial?
- Everything is good.

120
00:10:58.535 --> 00:10:59.536
Judge.

121
00:11:12.173 --> 00:11:14.133
I'm not feeling well.
so let's make this quick.

122
00:11:14.134 --> 00:11:16.552
I'm here about the investigation
into Trumbull.

123
00:11:16.553 --> 00:11:18.721
- I thought that was settled.
- It is.

124
00:11:18.722 --> 00:11:22.308
Well. this was found about ten hours ago
by Deputy Billings

125
00:11:22.309 --> 00:11:25.604
on a search we did with Deputy Karins.

126
00:11:26.187 --> 00:11:27.147
Where?

127
00:11:28.273 --> 00:11:30.692
Trumbull's apartment.
In the bathroom. sir.

128
00:11:31.610 --> 00:11:33.611
I'd like to conduct a relics investigation

129
00:11:33.612 --> 00:11:36.822
as a way to identify possible
offenders. like Trumbull.

130
00:11:36.823 --> 00:11:38.783
before they have a chance to act.

131
00:11:39.868 --> 00:11:43.787
Judge. the Pact says that the gateway
to disruptive criminal activity

132
00:11:43.788 --> 00:11:48.877
- often starts with unli...
- Unlicensed documents and relics. I know.

133
00:11:51.213 --> 00:11:52.755
But this relic. what is it?

134
00:11:52.756 --> 00:11:55.342
I don't know.
That's why I want to look into it.

135
00:11:55.842 --> 00:11:57.302
This didn't belong to Trumbull.

136
00:11:57.969 --> 00:12:00.513
I don't care where you found it.
It isn't his.

137
00:12:02.015 --> 00:12:06.143
You are aware we have files on every relic
found within the last 140 years.

138
00:12:06.144 --> 00:12:07.978
Yeah.
but I looked into the database. and...

139
00:12:07.979 --> 00:12:11.566
I wasn't saying "we" meaning all of us.
I mean "we" as in Judicial.

140
00:12:12.484 --> 00:12:14.986
We have a far more extensive catalog
of information.

141
00:12:15.570 --> 00:12:17.821
For example.
that watch you wear on your wrist.

142
00:12:17.822 --> 00:12:21.575
In Judicial. we know. I know.
that particular item.

143
00:12:21.576 --> 00:12:23.452
despite being in your possession.

144
00:12:23.453 --> 00:12:27.624
is currently registered
to a now-deceased George Wilkins.

145
00:12:28.541 --> 00:12:30.544
A man who you claim was murdered.

146
00:12:33.004 --> 00:12:34.130
Accidents happen.

147
00:12:35.048 --> 00:12:38.259
And Sheriff Becker made me realize
that Wilkins' death was one of them.

148
00:12:38.260 --> 00:12:40.803
That's why I'd like to open
this investigation.

149
00:12:40.804 --> 00:12:43.557
So that we can know those things
that are not in your catalog.

150
00:12:44.432 --> 00:12:47.476
Like the fact that your very close
colleague. Douglas Trumbull.

151
00:12:47.477 --> 00:12:49.103
- was a murderer.
- Sheriff Nichols.

152
00:12:49.104 --> 00:12:51.314
Judge. if I may?

153
00:12:51.940 --> 00:12:52.941
You may.

154
00:12:53.858 --> 00:12:57.195
Let's wrap it up. I wanna get home
before I have to fight through a crowd.

155
00:13:00.740 --> 00:13:03.909
A relics investigation
is actually a smart play.

156
00:13:03.910 --> 00:13:06.078
Especially today
with the Forgiveness Holiday.

157
00:13:06.079 --> 00:13:08.247
people will be more inclined
to turn over items

158
00:13:08.248 --> 00:13:11.125
without facing legal jeopardy.
So. I'm fine with it...

159
00:13:11.126 --> 00:13:13.586
- Okay.
- ...as long as you take Paul with you.

160
00:13:13.587 --> 00:13:17.047
You probably know less of the Pact
than my son does.

161
00:13:17.048 --> 00:13:20.175
You'll need a specialist with you
at all times. creating a list.

162
00:13:20.176 --> 00:13:23.722
Every offense. every relic
and the names of who has what.

163
00:13:24.306 --> 00:13:26.057
Yeah. of course.

164
00:13:36.276 --> 00:13:38.903
- What's the plan?
- You can head back up. See you in an hour.

165
00:13:38.904 --> 00:13:41.405
Sheriff. with Sims taking interest.

166
00:13:41.406 --> 00:13:44.825
Judicial will be watching you
everywhere you go. Every level.

167
00:13:44.826 --> 00:13:49.080
Either his guys or the whispering friends
of the Silo. And they could be anybody.

168
00:13:49.664 --> 00:13:52.542
So. like it or not.
today I'm with you all the way.

169
00:13:53.376 --> 00:13:56.670
I know a guy who's been busted for relics.
and he owes me one.

170
00:13:56.671 --> 00:13:57.756
Let's go.

171
00:14:21.029 --> 00:14:24.199
- Fuck me. Who'd I kill this time?
- I've got a relic question.

172
00:14:25.283 --> 00:14:26.743
For someone at this address?

173
00:14:28.161 --> 00:14:29.955
You coming out. or are we going in?

174
00:14:33.708 --> 00:14:36.335
Look. I don't know what Marnes
told you about me. but I'm a simple man.

175
00:14:36.336 --> 00:14:40.339
I paint walls. That's how I make
my living. I don't deal illegal relics.

176
00:14:40.340 --> 00:14:42.092
So. who do I see about legal ones?

177
00:14:44.511 --> 00:14:45.679
Couldn't say.

178
00:14:46.805 --> 00:14:48.139
I don't deal anymore.

179
00:14:48.848 --> 00:14:50.307
Especially things like that.

180
00:14:50.308 --> 00:14:51.434
A watch?

181
00:14:52.102 --> 00:14:54.728
- A working watch. Who the fuck are you?
- Hey.

182
00:14:54.729 --> 00:14:57.398
The old guys at least had the decency
to identify themselves.

183
00:14:57.399 --> 00:14:59.358
I'm Deputy Billings.
The new Deputy Sheriff.

184
00:14:59.359 --> 00:15:00.277
Like I give a fuck.

185
00:15:06.283 --> 00:15:08.701
Sheriff. I don't know what you're looking
for me to do. okay?

186
00:15:08.702 --> 00:15:11.787
But I feel like no matter what I say
or I don't say. you're gonna arrest me.

187
00:15:11.788 --> 00:15:13.581
No. not on the Forgiveness Holiday.

188
00:15:13.582 --> 00:15:15.040
Bullshit. You don't arrest me now.

189
00:15:15.041 --> 00:15:18.919
you put my name on a list put together
by Judicial-face here. And then what?

190
00:15:18.920 --> 00:15:22.256
One day. out of the blue.
I'm just doing law-abiding shit...

191
00:15:22.257 --> 00:15:24.383
- 'Cause you're just a simple man.
- Exactly.

192
00:15:24.384 --> 00:15:26.802
Then there's a knock on the door.
You know what? Not even.

193
00:15:26.803 --> 00:15:29.680
Maybe there's just a sheriff
with a crowbar.

194
00:15:29.681 --> 00:15:31.932
and I'm yanked out of my place
for something I didn't do.

195
00:15:31.933 --> 00:15:34.894
- So. no. I don't know anyone.
- You know what. Kennedy?

196
00:15:34.895 --> 00:15:37.187
This sheriff is the only reason
you're not in jail.

197
00:15:37.188 --> 00:15:39.189
And you are obviously having regrets.

198
00:15:39.190 --> 00:15:42.861
This is not about you.
We're looking into relics.

199
00:15:43.445 --> 00:15:49.575
That watch is a very peculiar relic
to be using to investigate all relics.

200
00:15:49.576 --> 00:15:52.286
And it's on your arm
not in an evidence bag.

201
00:15:52.287 --> 00:15:54.622
which makes me believe
that it's personal to you.

202
00:15:54.623 --> 00:15:55.874
And in my experience.

203
00:15:56.541 --> 00:16:00.169
people with badges doing things
for personal reasons

204
00:16:00.170 --> 00:16:02.464
tend to get other people hurt.

205
00:16:04.341 --> 00:16:07.052
So you're giving us a name.
or are we leaving with yours?

206
00:16:09.221 --> 00:16:10.347
Your choice.

207
00:16:11.806 --> 00:16:12.974
How about this?

208
00:16:13.975 --> 00:16:17.728
How about you give me the watch.
I try to sell it. and if I do.

209
00:16:17.729 --> 00:16:19.813
I'll give you the name
of the person I sold it to.

210
00:16:19.814 --> 00:16:21.149
How about this?

211
00:16:23.068 --> 00:16:24.652
Shit. Sheriff.

212
00:16:24.653 --> 00:16:26.195
Hey. All right.

213
00:16:26.196 --> 00:16:28.822
I need you and Holston Junior
to stop showing up here. okay?

214
00:16:28.823 --> 00:16:31.951
You know. I saw there's a lot of space
outside your apartment.

215
00:16:31.952 --> 00:16:33.285
Room enough for two beds.

216
00:16:33.286 --> 00:16:34.828
- Yeah.
- We could make ourselves at home.

217
00:16:34.829 --> 00:16:36.413
- We could move in.
- Come back every day?

218
00:16:36.414 --> 00:16:38.583
- Every day.
- Or you could give us a name.

219
00:16:41.920 --> 00:16:46.882
There's only one name that I can give you

220
00:16:46.883 --> 00:16:48.551
without destroying my livelihood.

221
00:16:48.552 --> 00:16:50.053
- As a painter?
- No.

222
00:16:50.762 --> 00:16:55.767
As a man who's had his family destroyed
by this fucking bullshit.

223
00:16:57.602 --> 00:16:59.020
You got a pen. Mr. Billingsley?

224
00:17:37.392 --> 00:17:40.769
Travel the Silo.
Today's for unity. family and friends.

225
00:17:40.770 --> 00:17:44.900
Happy Forgiveness Day.

226
00:17:46.484 --> 00:17:48.737
Travel the Silo. Happy Forgiveness Day.

227
00:17:59.581 --> 00:18:01.958
You know. people leave traces.

228
00:18:02.542 --> 00:18:05.629
History is just traces
of a whole lot of people

229
00:18:06.546 --> 00:18:08.215
over a whole lot of time.

230
00:18:08.924 --> 00:18:13.385
Everything from the shirt on my back
to the shoes on our feet.

231
00:18:13.386 --> 00:18:17.973
You know. if we wanted. we could pinpoint
the exact place that it was stitched

232
00:18:17.974 --> 00:18:20.226
- or the person who wore it last.
- Really?

233
00:18:20.227 --> 00:18:22.561
- The exact same?
- Yeah. uh-huh. Yes. the exact same.

234
00:18:22.562 --> 00:18:25.065
- You want tea? Yeah.
- Yeah. please.

235
00:18:26.149 --> 00:18:27.275
Sorry. Continue.

236
00:18:28.151 --> 00:18:31.154
- It's fascinating. though. right?
- Yeah. I mean. it's so fascinating.

237
00:18:31.738 --> 00:18:34.324
- You don't appreciate that?
- No. I do.

238
00:18:40.914 --> 00:18:44.750
Don't you ever think about the world
beyond the Silo?

239
00:18:44.751 --> 00:18:47.045
No. When would I have time to do that?

240
00:18:47.629 --> 00:18:51.549
Even now. I'm worried some idiot
is tightening the wrong bolts

241
00:18:51.550 --> 00:18:53.259
or misreading the pressure valve.

242
00:18:53.260 --> 00:18:54.718
You're looking at my beautiful face

243
00:18:54.719 --> 00:18:56.720
and thinking about some idiot
with his pressure bolts.

244
00:18:56.721 --> 00:18:58.681
- Pressure valve.
- Pressure valve.

245
00:18:58.682 --> 00:19:01.142
And yeah.
'cause your face kind of looks like one.

246
00:19:02.143 --> 00:19:04.895
Sounds like the kind of thing
women and men in Mechanical dream about.

247
00:19:04.896 --> 00:19:06.313
- Pressure valve.
- Oh. yeah?

248
00:19:06.314 --> 00:19:07.273
Definitely.

249
00:19:07.274 --> 00:19:10.109
You know. while you're down here
dreaming of your world beyond worlds...

250
00:19:10.110 --> 00:19:12.821
- You're the one that showed me this place.
- Yeah.

251
00:19:13.572 --> 00:19:17.366
But I'm the one in Mechanical.
keeping you dreamers alive.

252
00:19:17.367 --> 00:19:18.827
Is that so?

253
00:19:20.287 --> 00:19:21.329
Yeah.

254
00:19:22.747 --> 00:19:25.166
'Cause I'm the one
that keeps things running.

255
00:19:34.342 --> 00:19:38.054
- This must have taken you hours.
- Yeah. Time I don't have.

256
00:19:40.140 --> 00:19:41.141
So...

257
00:19:42.893 --> 00:19:43.894
why?

258
00:19:46.396 --> 00:19:48.815
'Cause when you talk about these things.

259
00:19:49.941 --> 00:19:54.612
something ignites in you.
and I can see it on your face.

260
00:19:54.613 --> 00:19:56.989
And I don't see that on a lot of people.

261
00:19:56.990 --> 00:20:02.537
And. you know. whatever that feeling is.

262
00:20:03.747 --> 00:20:06.666
when you feel it. I feel that too.

263
00:20:09.419 --> 00:20:11.963
And it's not just here.

264
00:20:12.547 --> 00:20:16.176
It's afterwards.

265
00:20:19.721 --> 00:20:20.722
It's...

266
00:20:22.098 --> 00:20:24.725
What I'm trying to say is.
I fixed your watch for selfish reasons

267
00:20:24.726 --> 00:20:29.272
'cause I really like the way that I feel
when I make you feel the way that you do.

268
00:20:32.651 --> 00:20:34.277
Hey. how'd you get it working?

269
00:20:35.445 --> 00:20:37.656
It was easy to fix once
I'd made the right tools.

270
00:20:38.156 --> 00:20:39.908
- You made the tools?
- Yeah.

271
00:20:41.910 --> 00:20:43.370
Juliette Nichols.

272
00:20:44.746 --> 00:20:48.541
you are truly...

273
00:20:49.251 --> 00:20:50.377
Okay. but...

274
00:20:51.545 --> 00:20:52.546
...incredible.

275
00:21:04.266 --> 00:21:05.475
I know.

276
00:21:07.644 --> 00:21:09.062
Soon. baby.

277
00:21:26.079 --> 00:21:27.080
Regina Jackson?

278
00:21:30.375 --> 00:21:31.376
Come in.

279
00:21:40.677 --> 00:21:42.762
Never thought I'd see that again.

280
00:21:43.513 --> 00:21:44.723
I'm sorry. what?

281
00:21:45.682 --> 00:21:46.933
That watch.

282
00:21:49.769 --> 00:21:50.770
You know it?

283
00:21:51.813 --> 00:21:54.566
Of course I do.
It belonged to my boyfriend.

284
00:22:23.845 --> 00:22:26.681
So. how is George?

285
00:22:29.226 --> 00:22:30.268
He's dead.

286
00:22:31.603 --> 00:22:33.939
He fell off the stairs a few months ago.

287
00:22:45.033 --> 00:22:47.994
Either of you know George.
or is the watch just something you found?

288
00:22:49.496 --> 00:22:51.665
No. I worked with him
before I became sheriff.

289
00:22:52.582 --> 00:22:54.334
- In Mechanical?
- Yeah.

290
00:22:59.005 --> 00:23:01.340
Ms. Jackson. are you in possession
of any relics? Legal...

291
00:23:01.341 --> 00:23:03.425
Last time I saw him.
that's where he was headed.

292
00:23:03.426 --> 00:23:04.970
Moving on to the next thing.

293
00:23:06.012 --> 00:23:07.013
The next person.

294
00:23:10.058 --> 00:23:13.269
No. I don't have any relics. Not anymore.

295
00:23:13.270 --> 00:23:17.566
Anything I had. and there was a lot.
I got for him.

296
00:23:20.193 --> 00:23:21.611
Somebody give you my name?

297
00:23:23.113 --> 00:23:24.531
Happens a lot.

298
00:23:25.407 --> 00:23:28.827
But I'm no dealer.
George had me buying things for him.

299
00:23:30.036 --> 00:23:34.249
I come from a big family.
Lots of aunts. uncles. cousins.

300
00:23:35.375 --> 00:23:39.421
He figured it would justify
the purchases if Judicial looked into it.

301
00:23:40.255 --> 00:23:43.257
He had no one. so he used me to get them.

302
00:23:43.258 --> 00:23:46.303
- All legal items? Or were there...
- Was your relationship sanctioned?

303
00:23:47.053 --> 00:23:49.681
George didn't do sanctioned relationships.

304
00:23:50.473 --> 00:23:53.685
And any fool would see he's not the type
of guy you spend forever with.

305
00:23:56.938 --> 00:24:00.984
Legal? Sure. I guess.
But how does anyone know?

306
00:24:01.568 --> 00:24:02.611
You ask.

307
00:24:03.445 --> 00:24:05.654
I walk into a law enforcement agency

308
00:24:05.655 --> 00:24:09.659
and ask if the item I now possess
is an illegal possession?

309
00:24:10.327 --> 00:24:11.994
Seems like I'm making it easy for them.

310
00:24:11.995 --> 00:24:16.625
Did you see or hear from him
after he went down to Mechanical?

311
00:24:17.876 --> 00:24:19.461
You ask a lot of questions.

312
00:24:21.379 --> 00:24:22.714
Look. Sheriff.

313
00:24:24.049 --> 00:24:27.510
George went down to Mechanical to explore
what he called "the big questions."

314
00:24:28.011 --> 00:24:29.303
Illegal questions.

315
00:24:29.304 --> 00:24:32.933
He got what he wanted from me.
He didn't need me anymore. so he left.

316
00:24:33.850 --> 00:24:38.063
Probably in pursuit of someone new
down deep who could give him a hand.

317
00:24:40.273 --> 00:24:42.107
What illegal questions
are we talking about?

318
00:24:42.108 --> 00:24:44.653
I've been over this time and again
with Judicial.

319
00:24:45.779 --> 00:24:48.198
Those aunts and uncles I told you about.
so have they.

320
00:24:49.199 --> 00:24:51.117
George and those relics cost me a lot.

321
00:24:51.826 --> 00:24:54.996
He lost his family.
but he didn't mind isolating me from mine.

322
00:24:58.667 --> 00:25:00.043
He was good with words.

323
00:25:04.172 --> 00:25:07.716
Thank you for your time. Ms. Jackson.

324
00:25:07.717 --> 00:25:10.262
- If you have any questions. we can def...
- I do.

325
00:25:15.934 --> 00:25:19.604
When he told you he loved you.
did you believe him?

326
00:25:24.985 --> 00:25:25.986
Thank you.

327
00:25:47.424 --> 00:25:49.258
There's no way
that woman's all there. right?

328
00:25:49.259 --> 00:25:51.343
Her place is like
the junk room at Recycling.

329
00:25:51.344 --> 00:25:52.971
And the smell of that cat food.

330
00:25:53.889 --> 00:25:55.139
You all right?

331
00:25:55.140 --> 00:25:56.892
Yeah. I'm great.

332
00:26:30.175 --> 00:26:31.509
We need the room.

333
00:26:45.482 --> 00:26:46.483
Come on. man.

334
00:26:59.120 --> 00:27:01.288
There's an interview
with a confidential informant

335
00:27:01.289 --> 00:27:04.458
that indicates the relic
you brought in earlier

336
00:27:04.459 --> 00:27:06.252
was an illegal possession

337
00:27:06.253 --> 00:27:09.339
belonging to your colleague.
George Wilkins.

338
00:27:11.424 --> 00:27:12.675
I don't understand.

339
00:27:12.676 --> 00:27:14.552
According to Judicial records.

340
00:27:14.553 --> 00:27:17.722
a search was conducted
of Wilkins's place before he died.

341
00:27:18.223 --> 00:27:20.267
In that search. they found nothing.

342
00:27:20.850 --> 00:27:21.850
But last night.

343
00:27:21.851 --> 00:27:25.480
Wilkins's relic mysteriously appeared
in Trumbull's apartment

344
00:27:25.981 --> 00:27:28.233
as a result
of a search coordinated by you.

345
00:27:28.942 --> 00:27:32.153
First time I ever saw that relic
was last night in Trumbull's place

346
00:27:32.821 --> 00:27:35.197
- when Billings showed it to me.
- Wait...

347
00:27:35.198 --> 00:27:39.743
Sims. George and I were friends.
Beyond this watch...

348
00:27:39.744 --> 00:27:40.954
Beyond that?

349
00:27:41.621 --> 00:27:43.498
I never received anything from him.

350
00:27:43.999 --> 00:27:46.960
especially something as ridiculous
as that thing.

351
00:27:53.383 --> 00:27:55.259
I have a question.

352
00:27:55.260 --> 00:27:56.844
For Mr. Sims.

353
00:27:56.845 --> 00:28:01.181
On the day Judicial searched
George Wilkins's apartment.

354
00:28:01.182 --> 00:28:04.768
was Trumbull a member of the search team?

355
00:28:04.769 --> 00:28:08.022
Mayor. the name of Judicial's search team
members are strictly confidential.

356
00:28:08.023 --> 00:28:09.106
You know that.

357
00:28:09.107 --> 00:28:11.901
I am in no way required
to reveal that information

358
00:28:11.902 --> 00:28:14.194
to the Sheriff's Department
or the Mayor's Office.

359
00:28:14.195 --> 00:28:16.281
But if Trumbull was on that search team.

360
00:28:17.115 --> 00:28:19.533
is it even slightly possible
that he simply thought

361
00:28:19.534 --> 00:28:23.495
that the artifact was a harmless curio
and decided to take it home for himself?

362
00:28:23.496 --> 00:28:25.623
You want me to entertain a hypothetical.

363
00:28:25.624 --> 00:28:29.252
- I'm not going to do that.
- Theoretically. it is possible. Yes?

364
00:28:33.256 --> 00:28:37.134
In your search.
did you find anything to explain

365
00:28:37.135 --> 00:28:41.139
why Trumbull would wanna
murder Marnes and Jahns?

366
00:28:42.641 --> 00:28:48.062
- No. Not yet. I...
- No. As far as everybody knows.

367
00:28:48.063 --> 00:28:51.900
Marnes and Jahns died of heart issues
brought on by walking the Silo.

368
00:28:52.943 --> 00:28:55.069
Any further investigation
might expose the truth.

369
00:28:55.070 --> 00:28:56.863
and that could prove destabilizing.

370
00:28:58.740 --> 00:29:00.491
I know not everyone believes this.

371
00:29:00.492 --> 00:29:05.580
but I've found that some mysteries
are best left

372
00:29:06.581 --> 00:29:07.832
unsolved.

373
00:29:09.876 --> 00:29:10.877
Mr. Sims.

374
00:29:32.274 --> 00:29:34.651
Thank you for not telling them
about me and George.

375
00:29:35.694 --> 00:29:38.280
Did you plant that relic so I'd find it?

376
00:29:41.324 --> 00:29:43.784
Your decision could've gotten me jailed
or even sent to clean.

377
00:29:43.785 --> 00:29:45.286
I wouldn't have let that happen.

378
00:29:45.287 --> 00:29:48.455
You brought up my name with them
just as soon as they came at you.

379
00:29:48.456 --> 00:29:53.587
Juliette. I have a family. A wife. a baby.

380
00:29:55.463 --> 00:29:57.506
I know having some Judicial-minded deputy

381
00:29:57.507 --> 00:30:00.342
who lives by every letter of the Pact
can be annoying.

382
00:30:00.343 --> 00:30:03.178
But you have to be honest with me.

383
00:30:03.179 --> 00:30:07.225
Honest. as if not only your life
but mine depended on it.

384
00:30:08.268 --> 00:30:09.269
I'll try.

385
00:30:10.520 --> 00:30:12.731
- You'll try?
- Yeah. That's what I can do.

386
00:30:13.773 --> 00:30:15.566
Juliette. you're the sheriff of the Silo.

387
00:30:15.567 --> 00:30:17.735
and you can't commit
to being honest with me?

388
00:30:17.736 --> 00:30:20.780
Shoot. maybe you and this George guy
were perfect for each other.

389
00:30:22.782 --> 00:30:24.868
- You want honesty?
- I do.

390
00:30:25.785 --> 00:30:28.370
Your hands shake.
You have flashes of pain.

391
00:30:28.371 --> 00:30:29.288
Sheriff...

392
00:30:29.289 --> 00:30:31.081
Under pressure.
you clench your hand so tight.

393
00:30:31.082 --> 00:30:32.708
I'm surprised your fingers don't fall off.

394
00:30:32.709 --> 00:30:33.960
You have the Syndrome.

395
00:30:35.795 --> 00:30:39.632
And you're hiding it. So. Deputy.
living by the letter of the Pact.

396
00:30:39.633 --> 00:30:42.384
you know it's a crime what you're doing.
not reporting yourself.

397
00:30:42.385 --> 00:30:44.220
- I do.
- And according to the Pact.

398
00:30:44.221 --> 00:30:47.139
you're in no way qualified
to be in a position of authority.

399
00:30:47.140 --> 00:30:49.391
to have access to a firearm.

400
00:30:49.392 --> 00:30:53.021
to detain criminals.
to even be a deputy in this department.

401
00:30:54.981 --> 00:30:56.524
There's a way to do this.

402
00:30:58.193 --> 00:31:00.153
And what you're doing now is not it.

403
00:31:00.862 --> 00:31:03.030
- You called me dishonest.
- I did not.

404
00:31:03.031 --> 00:31:04.406
- No?
- No.

405
00:31:04.407 --> 00:31:06.992
I only asked you to be honest.
and if you weren't gonna be.

406
00:31:06.993 --> 00:31:09.704
to let me know
rather than set me up to take the fall.

407
00:31:10.580 --> 00:31:14.333
Everybody in the office says the reason
Holston and Marnes were a great team

408
00:31:14.334 --> 00:31:16.043
was because they looked out
for each other.

409
00:31:16.044 --> 00:31:17.504
And look what that got them.

410
00:31:22.842 --> 00:31:24.177
Good night. Sheriff.

411
00:31:30.892 --> 00:31:32.227
Shit.

412
00:31:33.144 --> 00:31:34.812
- Hey. Happy Forgiveness Day.
- Hey.

413
00:31:34.813 --> 00:31:36.773
Happy Forgiveness Day. Deputy.

414
00:32:05.427 --> 00:32:06.678
How was your day?

415
00:32:10.056 --> 00:32:11.057
I've had better.

416
00:32:13.852 --> 00:32:15.020
No lights tonight?

417
00:32:16.980 --> 00:32:21.651
You know. my mother used to tell me
when I was a child that

418
00:32:22.652 --> 00:32:26.323
you shouldn't give up on the day.
even at the end of it. 'cause...

419
00:32:26.823 --> 00:32:30.785
Well. she said that a whole day
could be saved with just a smile.

420
00:32:33.955 --> 00:32:36.291
Lukas. you've never had a girlfriend.
have you?

421
00:32:38.126 --> 00:32:38.960
Tons.

422
00:32:38.961 --> 00:32:40.211
Not one.

423
00:32:40.212 --> 00:32:41.670
So many.

424
00:32:41.671 --> 00:32:46.218
Like. every other level.
there is another lady friend.

425
00:32:49.095 --> 00:32:51.013
And there. See?

426
00:32:51.014 --> 00:32:52.098
There see what?

427
00:32:52.682 --> 00:32:54.183
Smile. Like my mom said.

428
00:32:54.184 --> 00:32:57.187
This was not with you. This was at you.

429
00:32:58.230 --> 00:32:59.272
I'll still take it.

430
00:33:02.984 --> 00:33:05.320
You don't have your slate
with you tonight.

431
00:33:05.820 --> 00:33:08.322
Well. a cafeteria worker
on my level told me

432
00:33:08.323 --> 00:33:10.532
that it was gonna be cloudy
this evening. so I...

433
00:33:10.533 --> 00:33:12.160
You came up anyway?

434
00:33:13.036 --> 00:33:15.789
Yeah. I came to see you.

435
00:33:19.251 --> 00:33:21.585
Wow. that's terrible.

436
00:33:21.586 --> 00:33:23.796
- Wow.
- That is a good line.

437
00:33:23.797 --> 00:33:26.048
I didn't think it could get worse.
but you found a way.

438
00:33:26.049 --> 00:33:28.717
Okay. well. you're still smiling.
so whatever.

439
00:33:28.718 --> 00:33:30.971
Okay. I'll... Take care.

440
00:33:32.097 --> 00:33:34.099
See you tomorrow. Sheriff?

441
00:33:48.405 --> 00:33:49.406
Honey?

442
00:33:50.490 --> 00:33:52.117
Who's here?

443
00:33:55.412 --> 00:33:56.621
Oh. my goodness.

444
00:33:58.206 --> 00:33:59.165
Yeah.

445
00:34:00.250 --> 00:34:01.251
Yeah.

446
00:34:07.007 --> 00:34:08.508
- Hi.
- Hey.

447
00:34:13.512 --> 00:34:14.514
Look at you.

448
00:34:17.099 --> 00:34:20.310
How was your day? Daddy loves you.

449
00:34:20.311 --> 00:34:22.563
You okay? Look at your hands.

450
00:34:22.564 --> 00:34:24.983
- Yeah. I'm okay.
- Sit down.

451
00:34:26.818 --> 00:34:28.778
- Honey. please sit.
- Okay.

452
00:34:31.155 --> 00:34:32.157
Yeah.

453
00:34:33.867 --> 00:34:36.786
Take off your shirt.
Did you eat the ginger root I gave you?

454
00:34:38.329 --> 00:34:39.497
I couldn't.

455
00:34:41.166 --> 00:34:42.666
I wasn't alone at all today.

456
00:34:43.251 --> 00:34:44.836
She had you with her all day?

457
00:34:46.755 --> 00:34:47.963
Finally trust you?

458
00:34:49.758 --> 00:34:51.885
I don't think she's the trusting type.

459
00:34:52.552 --> 00:34:55.680
She'll come around.
She should be honored to have you.

460
00:35:20.205 --> 00:35:22.749
Honey. has it happened yet?

461
00:35:23.416 --> 00:35:24.501
What's that?

462
00:35:26.002 --> 00:35:27.462
Have you seen any signs in Claire?

463
00:35:28.547 --> 00:35:30.257
You know it doesn't work that way.

464
00:35:31.174 --> 00:35:33.510
Just because you have it
doesn't mean she will.

465
00:35:34.553 --> 00:35:35.595
But I worry.

466
00:35:36.888 --> 00:35:37.889
I know.

467
00:35:41.017 --> 00:35:45.355
But right now. let's just worry
about getting you fixed up

468
00:35:46.648 --> 00:35:48.275
so that you can get some sleep.

469
00:35:56.074 --> 00:35:57.075
Kath.

470
00:35:57.701 --> 00:36:00.620
- Honey. you don't need to...
- I'm thankful for you and Claire.

471
00:36:03.790 --> 00:36:07.294
I can't imagine life in the Silo
if I was all by myself.

472
00:36:35.947 --> 00:36:36.948
George?

473
00:36:38.909 --> 00:36:40.577
What's the big question?

474
00:36:43.079 --> 00:36:44.456
There's a lot of them.

475
00:36:48.251 --> 00:36:50.502
What's outside?

476
00:36:50.503 --> 00:36:54.841
What's beyond what the sensor can see?

477
00:36:57.135 --> 00:36:58.595
Why are we here?

478
00:36:59.304 --> 00:37:01.848
How long have we been here?

479
00:37:04.059 --> 00:37:06.353
How much time do we have left?

480
00:37:10.106 --> 00:37:12.150
But what's the biggest one?

481
00:37:18.907 --> 00:37:22.326
What if everything you know to be true.

482
00:37:22.327 --> 00:37:26.248
everything you've been told
by the people you love...

483
00:37:28.583 --> 00:37:34.130
was in fact just one big lie?

484
00:38:09.624 --> 00:38:10.625
Walk?

485
00:38:13.169 --> 00:38:14.170
<i>Walk?</i>

486
00:38:19.384 --> 00:38:21.595
Hey. it's late.

487
00:38:22.679 --> 00:38:24.055
Yeah. it's so quiet.

488
00:38:27.601 --> 00:38:28.977
It's time to come home.

489
00:38:32.397 --> 00:38:33.398
Yeah?

490
00:38:35.108 --> 00:38:38.695
Yeah. In the morning.
I'm gonna do what you said.

491
00:38:39.446 --> 00:38:41.615
I'm gonna turn in the badge and resign.

492
00:38:44.701 --> 00:38:47.287
So did you figure out what happened?

493
00:38:50.206 --> 00:38:51.875
No. couldn't give a fuck.

494
00:38:54.044 --> 00:38:57.589
Turns out the person I was doing it for
wasn't worth the trip. so...

495
00:38:59.591 --> 00:39:02.551
So did you leave here
and go all the way up top for him

496
00:39:02.552 --> 00:39:05.680
or 'cause it was the right thing to do?

497
00:39:06.973 --> 00:39:10.435
I mean. shit. the man's dead.
He didn't ask you to go up there.

498
00:39:14.314 --> 00:39:15.732
It's just... It's a waste of time.

499
00:39:16.608 --> 00:39:17.609
Time?

500
00:39:19.194 --> 00:39:21.321
You got no concept of time.

501
00:39:22.155 --> 00:39:23.657
You think you do. but you don't.

502
00:39:24.783 --> 00:39:27.452
<i>It's 'cause you got a whole lot more
ahead of you than behind.</i>

503
00:39:28.453 --> 00:39:30.955
<i>Time to you is just an idea.</i>

504
00:39:30.956 --> 00:39:37.169
<i>To me. it's years spent trapped
behind a closed door with memories.</i>

505
00:39:37.170 --> 00:39:40.006
<i>All your friends and loved ones
somewhere out there.</i>

506
00:39:40.757 --> 00:39:42.008
<i>the other side of it.</i>

507
00:39:43.593 --> 00:39:45.219
You can talk to me about time

508
00:39:45.220 --> 00:39:47.639
when you can't
bring yourself to step out the door.

509
00:39:50.559 --> 00:39:52.561
When seconds have become years.

510
00:39:55.063 --> 00:39:57.148
He's not the person I thought he was.

511
00:39:58.984 --> 00:40:00.777
What kind of a person are you?

512
00:40:02.737 --> 00:40:04.363
The man you loved was murdered.

513
00:40:04.364 --> 00:40:09.578
and now you're saying it's a waste of time
to find out why?

514
00:40:15.250 --> 00:40:16.917
See. I don't know what happened.

515
00:40:16.918 --> 00:40:20.255
but when you left here.
love had you trying to do the right thing.

516
00:40:21.089 --> 00:40:24.050
And now anger is making you give up?

517
00:40:25.552 --> 00:40:27.596
<i>Fear did the same thing to me.</i>

518
00:40:29.806 --> 00:40:31.433
And that is a waste of time.

519
00:40:37.105 --> 00:40:39.399
You're welcome to come here and join me.

520
00:40:41.818 --> 00:40:43.445
<i>Or you can stay where you are.</i>

521
00:40:44.905 --> 00:40:51.161
let go of whatever it is you're
wrestling with and finish the job.

522
00:40:51.912 --> 00:40:52.913
<i>It's your call.</i>

523
00:41:39.709 --> 00:41:41.794
You're going to be honest with me
this time.

524
00:41:41.795 --> 00:41:42.878
What was I before?

525
00:41:42.879 --> 00:41:45.923
You're the confidential informant.
the rat who gave up George.

526
00:41:45.924 --> 00:41:48.759
You're the one
who told Judicial about the hard drive.

527
00:41:48.760 --> 00:41:51.012
It's 'cause of you George is dead. Regina!

528
00:41:52.514 --> 00:41:54.391
- Just give me a second.
- Give you a second?

529
00:41:55.850 --> 00:41:56.685
You come to my door.

530
00:41:56.686 --> 00:41:59.688
- and you accuse me of betrayal.
- You told Judicial about George.

531
00:42:00.272 --> 00:42:02.273
- No. not them.
- No?

532
00:42:02.274 --> 00:42:04.942
Judicial come during the day.
They ask the easy questions.

533
00:42:04.943 --> 00:42:07.779
But the man who knows everything.
he comes at night.

534
00:42:09.239 --> 00:42:10.991
What? What are you ta...

535
00:42:19.583 --> 00:42:21.917
One night. I wake up.
and there's a man in my bedroom.

536
00:42:21.918 --> 00:42:23.919
I can't see anything.
The lamp's been unplugged.

537
00:42:23.920 --> 00:42:25.963
And he tells me to not move.

538
00:42:25.964 --> 00:42:27.548
He wants me to tell him everything.

539
00:42:27.549 --> 00:42:30.926
- To give up everybody. not just George.
- Regina. what do you...

540
00:42:30.927 --> 00:42:33.929
For every one question I wouldn't answer.
he'd threaten two people I loved.

541
00:42:33.930 --> 00:42:38.435
Two people I loved. My friends. my family.

542
00:42:39.603 --> 00:42:40.936
If I left the apartment.

543
00:42:40.937 --> 00:42:43.188
he'd turn up at night
at the foot of my bed in the darkness.

544
00:42:43.189 --> 00:42:46.526
and he would recite the names of everyone
that I had talked to that day.

545
00:42:47.027 --> 00:42:48.445
Everyone I had talked to.

546
00:42:49.362 --> 00:42:50.780
If I had visitors...

547
00:42:52.240 --> 00:42:56.119
Look. I put these up to block the sound.
I don't know if it works.

548
00:42:56.828 --> 00:42:59.246
- Even with them. he may hear every word.
- Who is "he"?

549
00:42:59.247 --> 00:43:00.915
Regina. who are you talking about?

550
00:43:00.916 --> 00:43:04.669
They know how to get to you.
They know what you fear.

551
00:43:06.963 --> 00:43:07.964
My mother...

552
00:43:10.592 --> 00:43:14.346
every name I gave that man was another day
she didn't have to spend in the mines.

553
00:43:15.055 --> 00:43:19.017
So yeah. I gave up
the names of every relic dealer I knew.

554
00:43:23.063 --> 00:43:26.775
That's why Kennedy gave me your name.
Because he knew Judicial already had it.

555
00:43:29.110 --> 00:43:31.403
Well. hopefully they all know
so they'll stay away from here.

556
00:43:31.404 --> 00:43:34.531
- But if you cared for George...
- He only cared about himself.

557
00:43:34.532 --> 00:43:37.701
Hey. George is dead
'cause you gave up his name.

558
00:43:37.702 --> 00:43:40.496
He is dead
'cause he didn't give up the hard drive.

559
00:43:40.497 --> 00:43:42.290
The fucking hard drive.

560
00:43:43.458 --> 00:43:45.877
- Regina. what's on the hard drive?
- Don't ask.

561
00:43:47.003 --> 00:43:48.755
What's on the drive?

562
00:43:51.841 --> 00:43:52.842
I never saw.

563
00:44:04.354 --> 00:44:06.064
He never really cared about me.

564
00:44:08.233 --> 00:44:09.818
He used me to get it for him.

565
00:44:11.319 --> 00:44:12.653
Probably did the same to you.

566
00:44:12.654 --> 00:44:14.614
pretending to love you
to get what he wanted.

567
00:44:17.409 --> 00:44:18.577
I didn't give it to him.

568
00:44:20.036 --> 00:44:21.830
Then he gave me something from his mother.

569
00:44:23.373 --> 00:44:24.791
The only thing he kept of hers.

570
00:44:26.793 --> 00:44:27.836
What did he give you?

571
00:44:31.923 --> 00:44:36.595
These things. these objects. all this...

572
00:44:39.014 --> 00:44:40.265
stuff.

573
00:44:44.769 --> 00:44:46.813
Because of it. I have nothing.

574
00:44:52.485 --> 00:44:53.862
I have no one.

575
00:45:01.286 --> 00:45:04.663
I'm sure the hard drive's been destroyed.

576
00:45:04.664 --> 00:45:08.835
so I don't think
they're gonna disturb you anymore.

577
00:45:09.836 --> 00:45:11.254
Neither will I. so...

578
00:45:24.726 --> 00:45:25.727
Hey...

579
00:45:28.521 --> 00:45:30.439
what did George give up
for the hard drive?

580
00:45:30.440 --> 00:45:32.192
You said he gave you something.

581
00:45:34.569 --> 00:45:36.070
What is it?

582
00:45:36.071 --> 00:45:37.781
It's everything.

583
00:45:39.991 --> 00:45:41.868
I don't think they know it exists.

584
00:45:44.329 --> 00:45:46.288
They search and toss my place.

585
00:45:46.289 --> 00:45:51.086
They look under the mat.
but they just toss the damn thing aside.

586
00:46:00.845 --> 00:46:01.845
What is that?

587
00:46:01.846 --> 00:46:07.184
This is a gift from George's mother.
given to him by his aunt. Gloria.

588
00:46:07.185 --> 00:46:10.187
This was passed down
and hidden for generations.

589
00:46:10.188 --> 00:46:12.566
Is this before the rebellion?

590
00:46:13.358 --> 00:46:17.571
Was before the Silo.
Before there was a reason to lie.

591
00:46:25.453 --> 00:46:28.790
When you see what you'll see.
don't speak it out loud.

592
00:46:29.457 --> 00:46:30.667
Don't let them hear.

593
00:46:32.502 --> 00:46:35.130
This will get you killed.

594
00:49:13.038 --> 00:49:14.456
You have to wake him up.

595
00:49:16.041 --> 00:49:18.208
But it's the middle of the night.

596
00:49:18.209 --> 00:49:20.962
I know. but he has to see this.

597
00:49:22.839 --> 00:49:23.840
Now.

597
00:49:24.305 --> 00:50:24.280
